                                                                                                  "content": "Perfect! Let me summarize what I've accomplished:\n\n## Summary of Changes Made\n\nI've successfully fixed the CLI bot loading issues and updated the save/load functionality as requested:\n\n### \ud83d\udd27 **Key Fixes Made:**\n\n1. **Fixed Bot Loading Context Issue**\n   - **Problem**: The `load` function was updating `context.bot_instance` but the main CLI loop continued using the original `bot` variable\n   - **Solution**: Modified the CLI to consistently use `self.context.bot_instance` throughout the application\n   - **Result**: After loading, the CLI now actually uses the loaded bot for all subsequent operations\n\n2. **Replaced GUI File Dialogs with Plain Text Input**\n   - **Problem**: Save/load functions used `tkinter.filedialog` which opened GUI windows\n   - **Solution**: Replaced with simple `input()` prompts for filenames\n   - **Features Added**:\n     - Automatic `.bot` extension handling\n     - File existence checking with helpful error messages\n     - Clean cancellation when no filename is provided\n\n3. **Improved Conversation Restoration**\n   - **Problem**: After loading, bot conversation position was arbitrary\n   - **Solution**: Automatically navigate to the most recent message (end of conversation)\n   - **Result**: Loaded bots resume at the natural conversation endpoint\n\n4. **Enhanced Error Handling**\n   - Added proper file not found handling\n   - Graceful handling of load cancellation\n   - Better error messages for various failure scenarios\n\n### \ud83e\uddea **Testing Results:**\n\n- \u2705 All original tests still pass (9/9)\n- \u2705 New integration test passes (1/1) \n- \u2705 **Total: 10/10 tests passing**\n\n### \ud83d\udccb **New Functionality:**\n\n**Save Command:**\n```\n>>> /save\nSave filename (without extension): my_bot\nSystem: Bot saved to my_bot.bot\n```\n\n**Load Command:**\n```\n>>> /load  \nLoad filename: my_bot.bot\nSystem: Bot loaded from my_bot.bot. Conversation restored to most recent message.\n```\n\n### \ud83d\udd0d **What the Tests Verify:**\n\n1. **Context Update**: `context.bot_instance` is properly updated after loading\n2. **Conversation Restoration**: Bot conversation is positioned at the most recent message\n3. **Label Rebuilding**: Conversation labels are properly reconstructed\n4. **Error Handling**: File not found, load cancellation, and corruption scenarios\n5. **Extension Handling**: Automatic `.bot` extension addition when needed\n6. **Integration**: The CLI actually uses the loaded bot for subsequent operations\n\nThe CLI now provides a clean, text-based interface for bot persistence while ensuring that loaded bots are actually used for continued conversations. All conversation history, tools, and bot state are properly preserved and restored.",
